{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}} {{Portuguese name|Domingues|Aganzo}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Milene Domingues | image = | fullname = Milene Domingues Aganzo | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1979|6|18}} | birth_place = [[São Paulo (city)|São Paulo]], Brazil | height = 1.67 m | currentclub = | clubnumber = | position = [[Midfielder]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 1997–2001 | years2 = 2001–2002 | years3 = 2002–2004 | years4 = 2004–2007 | years5 = 2007–2009 | clubs1 = [[Sport Club Corinthians Paulista|SC Corinthians]] | clubs2 = [[ASD Fiammamonza]] | clubs3 = [[Rayo Vallecano Femenino|Rayo Vallecano]] | clubs4 = [[AD Torrejón CF (women)|AD Torrejón CF]] | clubs5 = [[CF Pozuelo de Alarcón Femenino|CF Pozuelo]] | caps1 = 118 | caps2 = 23 | caps3 = 11 | caps4 = 70 | caps5 = 36 | goals1 = 60 | goals2 = 8 | goals3 = 1 | goals4 = 22 | goals5 = 3 | nationalyears1 = 2003–2006 | nationalteam1 = [[Brazil women's national football team|Brazil]] | nationalcaps1 = 20 | nationalgoals1 = 9 | club-update = | nationalteam-update = }}
'''Milene Domingues Aganzo''' (born 18 June 1979) is a Brazilian former [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[midfielder]].
==Career== Born in [[São Paulo (city)|São Paulo]], Domingues was first signed by [[Sport Club Corinthians Paulista|SC Corinthians]] and last for [[CF Pozuelo de Alarcón]]. The ex-model also holds the women's record for [[Keepie uppie|ball juggling]], keeping a football off the ground with 55,198 touches.<ref>[http://www2.uol.com.br/simbolo/corpoacorpo/0101/milene.htm Brazilian magazine '''Corpo A Corpo''' article about Milene Domingues] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050408212712/http://www2.uol.com.br/simbolo/corpoacorpo/0101/milene.htm |date=8 April 2005 }}</ref> She was also the most expensive female football player in Spain, costing over £200,000.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/europe/2253370.stm Mrs Ronaldo in record transfer] BBC Sports 12 September 2002. Retrieved 18 February 2007.</ref>
At international level she represented the [[Brazil women's national football team]] at the [[2003 Women's World Cup]].
==Personal life== She was married to [[association football|football]] star [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]] from April 1999 to September 2003.<ref>[http://www.elmundo.es/cronica/2002/362/1032770100.html El equipo de «Ronaldinha»»]</ref> Together they have one son, Ronald, who was born in [[Milan]], on 6 April 2000. She is a [[Buddhist]].
