The following is the family tree of the Spanish monarchs starting from [[Isabella I of Castile|Isabella of Castile]] and [[Ferdinand II of Aragon|Ferdinand of Aragon]] till the present day.
The former kingdoms of [[Crown of Aragon|Aragon]], [[Crown of Castile|Castile]] (see [[Monarchs of Castile family tree|family tree]]) and [[Kingdom of Navarre|Navarre]] (see [[Kings of Navarre family tree|family tree]]) were independent kingdoms that [[Catholic Monarchs|unified]] in the 15th century to become the Kingdom of [[Spain]].

